{"title_page": "Hameed Hussain Sheikh Ismail", "text_new": "{{more citations needed|date=January 2018}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|honorific-prefix   = [[The Honourable|Hon.]]\n|name               = Hameed Hussain Sheikh Ismail\n|native_name        = \n|native_name_lang   =\n|honorific-suffix   = [[Order of the British Empire|MBE]]\n|image              = \n|imagesize          = \n|smallimage         = <!--If this is specified, \"image\" should not be.-->\n|alt                = \n|caption            = \n| order               = \n| constituency_MP     = [[Puttalam Electoral District (1947\u20131989)|Puttalam]]\n| parliament          = Ceylon\n| majority            =<!-- Can be repeated up to eight times by adding a number -->\n| term_start          = 1947\n| term_end            = 1960\n| predecessor         = seat created\n| successor           = [[M. H. Naina Marikkar]]\n|order1              = [[List of Speakers of the Parliament of Sri Lanka|5th Speaker of the Parliament]]\n|office1             = \n|term_start1         = 19 April 1956\n|term_end1           = 5 December 1959\n|primeminister1      = [[John Kotelawala]]<br>[[S. W. R. D. Bandaranaike]]<br>[[Wijeyananda Dahanayake]]\n|predecessor1        = [[Albert Peries]]\n|successor1          = [[Tikiri Banda Subasinghe]]\n|birth_date         = {{birth date|1901|05|19|df=y}}\n|birth_place        = [[Puttalam]]\n|death_date         = {{Death date and age|1974|8|3|1901|05|19|df=yes}}\n|death_place        = \n|restingplace       = \n|restingplacecoordinates = \n|birthname          = \n|citizenship        = \n|nationality        = \n|party              = [[Independent (politician)|Independent]]\n|otherparty         =  <!--For additional political affiliations-->\n|spouse             = \n|partner            =  <!--For those with a domestic partner and not married-->\n|relations          = \n|children           = \n|residence          = \n|alma_mater         = \n|occupation         = \n|profession         = \n|cabinet            = \n|committees         = \n|portfolio          = \n|religion           = \n|signature          = \n|signature_alt      = \n|website            = \n}}\n\n'''Hameed Hussain Sheikh Ismail''', [[Order of the British Empire|MBE]] (19 May 1901 - 3 August 1974) was a [[Sri Lanka]]n lawyer and politician. He was the [[List of Speakers of the Parliament of Sri Lanka|5th]] [[Speaker of the Parliament of Sri Lanka]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Ismail, Hameed Hussain Sheikh|url=http://www.parliament.lk/en/component/members/viewMember/2325?Itemid=206|publisher=Parliament.lk|accessdate=30 December 2013}}</ref> \n\n==Early life and education==\nBorn in [[Puttalam]] to a middle class family, started his [[Quran|Qur\u2019anic]] lessons in 1905. He was educated at St. Andrew\u2019s College, Puttalam and at [[Wesley College, Colombo]]. He entered the [[Ceylon Law College]], and passed the Proctor\u2019s Finals exams in 1925 wining several prizes.<ref name=\"Island\">{{cite news |last1=Azwer |first1=Alhaj A. H. M. |title=The Golden Plain - Life and times of Alhaj H. S. Ismail |url=http://www.island.lk/2003/05/25/featur10.html |accessdate=21 April 2020 |publisher=Island}}</ref> \n\n==Legal career==\nHaving qualified as a [[Proctor]], Ismail started his legal practice in Colombo, but soon moved it to his home town of Puttalam.<ref name=\"Island\"/>\n\n==Political career==\nEntering local politics, Ismail was elected member of the Puttalam Local Board in 1929 and member of the Puttalam Urban Council in 1933 and served as Chairmen of the Puttalam Urban Council from 1936 to 1947. He was elected un-contested in the [[1947 Ceylonese parliamentary election|1947 general election]] from the [[Puttalam Electoral District (1947\u20131989)|Puttalam electorate]] as an [[Independent politician|independent candidate]] to the [[Parliament of Ceylon]]. Soon after he was appointed by Prime Minister [[D. S. Senanayake]] as [[Parliamentary Secretary]] to the Minister of Food and Co-operative Undertakings. In 1948, he was elected Vice President of the All Ceylon Muslim League. Elected in the [[1952 Ceylonese parliamentary election|1952 general election]], he was elected Deputy Speaker and the Deputy Chairman of Committees serving till 1956 and was elected Speaker following the [[1956 Ceylonese parliamentary election|1956 general election]], serving till 1959. In 1961, he was elected President of the All Ceylon Muslim League. He was appointed [[Member of the Order of the British Empire]] (MBE) in the [[1949_New_Year_Honours#Member_of_the_Order_of_the_British_Empire_(MBE)_2|1949 New Year Honours]].<ref name=\"Island\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.parliament.lk/en/component/members/viewMember/2325?Itemid=206 Hameed Hussain Sheikh Ismail]\n*[http://www.parliament.lk/en/speakers Speaker of the Parliament]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before={{nowrap|[[Albert Peries]]}}}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Speaker of the Parliament of Sri Lanka|Speaker of the Parliament]]|years=1956\u20131959}}\n{{s-aft|after={{nowrap|[[Tikiri Banda Subasinghe]]}}}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Sri Lankan Speakers of Parliament}}\n{{Members of 1st Parliament of Ceylon}}\n{{Members of 2nd Parliament of Ceylon}}\n{{Members of 3rd Parliament of Ceylon}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1901 births]]\n[[Category:1974 deaths]]\n[[Category:Speakers of the Parliament of Sri Lanka]]\n[[Category:Deputy speakers and chairmen of committees of the Parliament of Sri Lanka]]\n[[Category:Deputy chairmen of committees of the Parliament of Sri Lanka]]\n[[Category:Parliamentary secretaries of Ceylon]]\n[[Category:Ceylonese Members of the Order of the British Empire]]\n[[Category:Ceylonese proctors]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Wesley College, Colombo]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Ceylon Law College]]\n", "text_old": "{{more citations needed|date=January 2018}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|honorific-prefix   = [[The Honourable]]\n|name               = Hameed Hussain Sheikh Ismail\n|native_name        = \n|native_name_lang   =\n|honorific-suffix   = [[MBE]]\n|image              = \n|imagesize          = \n|smallimage         = <!--If this is specified, \"image\" should not be.-->\n|alt                = \n|caption            = \n| order               = \n| constituency_MP     = [[Puttalam Electoral District (1947\u20131989)|Puttalam]]\n| parliament          = Ceylon\n| majority            =<!-- Can be repeated up to eight times by adding a number -->\n| term_start          = 1947\n| term_end            = 1960\n| predecessor         = seat created\n| successor           = [[M. H. Naina Marikkar]]\n|order1              = [[List of Speakers of the Parliament of Sri Lanka|5th Speaker of the Parliament]]\n|office1             = \n|term_start1         = 19 April 1956\n|term_end1           = 5 December 1959\n|primeminister1      = [[John Kotelawala]]<br>[[S. W. R. D. Bandaranaike]]<br>[[Wijeyananda Dahanayake]]\n|predecessor1        = [[Albert Peries]]\n|successor1          = [[Tikiri Banda Subasinghe]]\n|birth_date         = {{birth date|1901|05|19|df=y}}\n|birth_place        = [[Puttalam]]\n|death_date         = {{Death date and age|1974|8|3|1901|05|19|df=yes}}\n|death_place        = \n|restingplace       = \n|restingplacecoordinates = \n|birthname          = \n|citizenship        = \n|nationality        = \n|party              = [[Independent (politician)|Independent]]\n|otherparty         =  <!--For additional political affiliations-->\n|spouse             = \n|partner            =  <!--For those with a domestic partner and not married-->\n|relations          = \n|children           = \n|residence          = \n|alma_mater         = \n|occupation         = \n|profession         = \n|cabinet            = \n|committees         = \n|portfolio          = \n|religion           = \n|signature          = \n|signature_alt      = \n|website            = \n}}\n\n'''Hameed Hussain Sheikh Ismail''', [[MBE]] (19 May 1901 - 3 August 1974) was a [[Sri Lanka]]n lawyer and politician. He was the [[List of Speakers of the Parliament of Sri Lanka|5th]] [[Speaker of the Parliament of Sri Lanka]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Ismail, Hameed Hussain Sheikh|url=http://www.parliament.lk/en/component/members/viewMember/2325?Itemid=206|publisher=Parliament.lk|accessdate=30 December 2013}}</ref> \n\n==Early life and education==\nBorn in [[Puttalam]] to a middle class family, started his [[Quran|Qur\u2019anic]] lessons in 1905. He was educated at St. Andrew\u2019s College, Puttalam and at [[Wesley College, Colombo]]. He entered the [[Ceylon Law College]], and passed the Proctor\u2019s Finals exams in 1925 wining several prizes.<ref name=\"Island\">{{cite news |last1=Azwer |first1=Alhaj A. H. M. |title=The Golden Plain - Life and times of Alhaj H. S. Ismail |url=http://www.island.lk/2003/05/25/featur10.html |accessdate=21 April 2020 |publisher=Island}}</ref> \n\n==Legal career==\nHaving qualified as a [[Proctor]], Ismail started his legal practice in Colombo, but soon moved it to his home town of Puttalam.<ref name=\"Island\"/>\n\n==Political career==\nEntering local politics, Ismail was elected member of the Puttalam Local Board in 1929 and member of the Puttalam Urban Council in 1933 and served as Chairmen of the Puttalam Urban Council from 1936 to 1947. He was elected un-contested in the [[1947 Ceylonese parliamentary election|1947 general election]] from the [[Puttalam Electoral District (1947\u20131989)|Puttalam electorate]] as an [[Independent politician|independent candidate]] to the [[Parliament of Ceylon]]. Soon after he was appointed by Prime Minister [[D. S. Senanayake]] as [[Parliamentary Secretary]] to the Minister of Food and Co-operative Undertakings. In 1948, he was elected Vice President of the All Ceylon Muslim League. Elected in the [[1952 Ceylonese parliamentary election|1952 general election]], he was elected Deputy Speaker and the Deputy Chairman of Committees serving till 1956 and was elected Speaker following the [[1956 Ceylonese parliamentary election|1956 general election]], serving till 1959. In 1961, he was elected President of the All Ceylon Muslim League. He was appointed [[Member of the Order of the British Empire]] (MBE) in the [[1949_New_Year_Honours#Member_of_the_Order_of_the_British_Empire_(MBE)_2|1949 New Year Honours]].<ref name=\"Island\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.parliament.lk/en/component/members/viewMember/2325?Itemid=206 Hameed Hussain Sheikh Ismail]\n*[http://www.parliament.lk/en/speakers Speaker of the Parliament]\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before={{nowrap|[[Albert Peries]]}}}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Speaker of the Parliament of Sri Lanka|Speaker of the Parliament]]|years=1956\u20131959}}\n{{s-aft|after={{nowrap|[[Tikiri Banda Subasinghe]]}}}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Sri Lankan Speakers of Parliament}}\n{{Members of 1st Parliament of Ceylon}}\n{{Members of 2nd Parliament of Ceylon}}\n{{Members of 3rd Parliament of Ceylon}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1901 births]]\n[[Category:1974 deaths]]\n[[Category:Speakers of the Parliament of Sri Lanka]]\n[[Category:Deputy speakers and chairmen of committees of the Parliament of Sri Lanka]]\n[[Category:Deputy chairmen of committees of the Parliament of Sri Lanka]]\n[[Category:Parliamentary secretaries of Ceylon]]\n[[Category:Ceylonese Members of the Order of the British Empire]]\n[[Category:Ceylonese proctors]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Wesley College, Colombo]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Ceylon Law College]]\n", "name_user": "Dan arndt", "label": "safe", "comment": "As per outcomes of previous detailed discussion", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hameed_Hussain_Sheikh_Ismail"}
